      "value": "Poway Unified is a K-12 unified district serving 5,511 students with active IEPs, including 1,314 autistic students. About 43% of autistic students spend 80% or more of the school day in general-education settings, lower than the 66% rate across all disability categories. Around 3.5% of autistic students are placed in fully separate special-education environments."
    },
    "what_this_means_for_parents": {
      "ai_disclaimer": "This summary was written by an AI model from the data points in this profile. The underlying numbers come from public California government sources, but the narrative is AI-written and may contain inaccuracies. Verify specific claims directly with the school district before making decisions.",
