      "ai_generated_at": "2026-05-16T07:19:45Z",
      "ai_model": "claude-opus (via Claude Code session)",
      "based_on_sources": [
        "cde_spedps",
        "ca_dashboard"
      ],
      "value": "For an autistic child, the data shows full-day general-education placement is less common than partial-day or specialized placement, with under half of autistic students in general-education settings 80% or more of the school day. District-wide academic performance is strong \u2014 56 points above standard in English and 40 points above in math for all students \u2014 though Students with Disabilities (a broader group that includes autism but is not autism-specific) sit 44 points below standard in English and 66 points below in math. Chronic absenteeism for SWD is 15%, roughly double the 9% rate for all students, and SWD suspensions are 3% compared to 1% district-wide. Inclusion rates are noticeably lower for autistic students (43%) than for the broader SWD group (66%), so placement patterns appear to differ by disability category."
    }
